War in Gaza: Hamas agrees to ceasefire proposal, Israel reviews accord
description: By Tuesday morning, Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu's government had neither approved nor rejected the agreement accepted the previous day by Hamas. Put forward by Egypt and Qatar, the proposal called first for a 60-day truce in exchange, notably, for the release of 10 live hostages, as well as a partial withdrawal of the Israeli army.

headline: 'By choosing AI for its remembrance policy, the French government is automating an intellectual process'
description: Historian Frédéric Clavert writes that the use of artificial intelligence (AI) by French ministries to create commemorative videos can result in highly questionable outcomes.

headline: The third life of a synagogue transformed into a contemporary art center
description: 'Unusual Places for an Exhibition' (1/6). Le Monde explores six art centers housed in unexpected venues. Today: a former sanctuary that was blown up by the Nazis and rebuilt after the war.

headline: 'What I would give to inhabit again a country where the gravest offense the president could be accused of was sartorial misconduct'
description: 'Letters from America' (2/6). Writer and journalist Thomas Chatterton Williams looks back at the 'ludicrous drama' caused by Barack Obama's tan suit in 2014. The contrast with Donald Trump's gaffes is striking.

headline: A winemaker, his daughter and a vintage for their undocumented workers
description: In southeastern France, Philippe Grisard and his daughter, Nadège, rely daily on undocumented workers to help tend their vineyard. To draw attention to their workers' precarious legal status, they named one of their vintages 'Sans eux' ('Without Them').

headline: The lobo-guará, Brazil's maned wolf, a national icon under threat
description: Emblematic of the Cerrado, these animals have seen their habitat fragmented by deforestation and the spread of industrial agriculture. In the state of Minas Gerais, a sanctuary now shelters some of them, aiming to raise public awareness.
